Schema Type
Star Schema

The project uses a Star Schema design where a central fact table (Sales_Fact) is connected to multiple dimension tables such as Date, Product, Customer, and Region. This improves performance and simplifies analysis.
Explanation
Data Cleaning:
- Removed duplicate values
- Handled missing/null values
- Converted data types (Date, Number, Text)

Data Modeling:
- Created Fact Table (Sales_Fact)
- Created Dimension Tables (Date, Product, Customer, Region)
- Applied Star Schema
- Maintained One-to-Many relationships
- Used Single Cross Filter Direction

Relationships:
- Connected dimension tables to fact table
- Created inactive relationship (Returns Date)
- Used USERELATIONSHIP() in DAX

DAX Measures:
- Total Sales
- Total Profit
- Total Orders
- Average Sales

Hierarchies:
- Date: Year → Quarter → Month → Day
- Product: Category → Sub-category → Product
- Region: Country → State → City

Visualizations:
- Bar Chart: Sales by Category
- Line Chart: Sales Trend
- Map: Region-wise Sales
- Table: Detailed Data
What Teacher Will Check
- Model View (relationships)
- Report View (visuals working)
- Clean structure
Conclusion
This project demonstrates building a Star Schema data model, applying DAX functions, and creating interactive dashboards in Power BI.
Tools Used
Power BI Desktop
DAX
